メソッドの詳細

canFilter

public boolean canFilter()
インタフェース ClassLoaderFilter の記述:
This method examines the environment to determine if it can be used to filter by ClassLoader. For example, a realization of this class for Tomcat might look for Tomcat's VM parameters to determine if the Tomcat is running in the VM.

定義:
インタフェース ClassLoaderFilter 内の canFilter

accept

public boolean accept(java.lang.ClassLoader loader)
インタフェース ClassLoaderFilter の記述:
Tries to determine if the given ClassLoader is the "application classloader". What this means exactly is dependent on the type of application (that is, this is different for Tomcat than for a standalone app)
